Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.18,0:00:04.48,Narr,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}Together with the Detective Boys, Ran and company,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.48,0:00:07.40,Narr,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}I boarded the Bell Tree Express.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.77,0:00:12.36,Narr,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}Suspicious passengers gathered in Carriage 8.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.24,0:00:16.41,Narr,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}And then, the deduction quiz taking place aboard the train
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.41,0:00:20.37,Narr,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}unexpectedly turned into a locked room murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.62,0:00:25.58,Narr,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}Meanwhile, a black shadow closes in on Haibara.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.58,0:00:30.34,Narr,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}And the identity of the man with a burn who kidnapped Sera is revealed...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.39,0:00:39.56,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Seeking comprehensive answers,\N he solves every mystery and code!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.56,0:00:41.39,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Their trap throws the train into a panic!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.39,0:00:43.98,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Haibara's fate hangs in the balance!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.98,0:00:45.90,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.90,0:00:47.69,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.69,0:00:49.69,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.59,0:02:41.97,Dialogue,,1,1,20,,But Detective, some of your deductions are hard to believe...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.47,0:02:46.14,Dialogue,,1,1,20,,It's not easy to add links to a chain lock.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.77,0:02:49.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\a6}And if the lamp above my room had been working,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.56,0:02:51.81,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,{\a6}the conductor wouldn't have come to my room in the first place!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.06,0:02:58.61,Signs,,0,0,0,,Mari Idenami (33)\NPassenger in Carriage 8, Room E
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.81,0:02:58.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\a6}And I only called the conductor because {\a6}the alarm rang on a watch that just happened to be left in my room!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.61,0:03:02.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{Conductor.} Mr. Conductor, you said it yourself, earlier, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.32,0:03:05.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That one of the conductors' uniforms was missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.95,0:03:07.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.16,0:03:10.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was probably Andō-{\i1}san{\i0}'s doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.66,0:03:14.96,Signs,,0,0,0,,Satoru Andō (41)\NPassenger in Carriage 8, Room C
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.62,0:03:14.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\a6}If he wore that uniform and snuck aboard the train amidst the pre-boarding checks...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.50,0:03:21.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then he could add a link to the chain lock of the crime scene,\N replace the bulb for Noto-{\i1}san{\i0}'s room with a broken one
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.76,0:03:25.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and hide the watch in Idenami-{\i1}san{\i0}'s room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.18,0:03:30.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if he remotely made the watch's alarm ring
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.39,0:03:34.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,while Idenami-{\i1}san{\i0} was arguing with the conductor to distract him,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.19,0:03:36.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then Andō-{\i1}san{\i0}, hiding in Room B,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.73,0:03:40.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,wouldn't be noticed
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.61,0:03:42.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,using the fishing line to open the mirrored Room C door.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.61,0:03:47.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then after locking Room B's chain lock under cover of the mirrored door,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.49,0:03:51.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then all he had to do was close the mirrored door as though he'd just come out of his room
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.50,0:03:54.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and approach Idenami-{\i1}san{\i0} and the conductor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.04,0:03:57.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, you managed to create a situation where though the conductor never left the corridor,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.92,0:04:03.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he never saw anyone going in or out of the crime scene!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.01,0:04:07.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unluckily, just before you opened the mirrored door,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.89,0:04:13.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Komino-{\i1}san{\i0} and her maid left their room and could've discovered the fishing line,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.35,0:04:16.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but in the darkness of the tunnel, it probably slipped their notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.90,0:04:22.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At least, I hope they didn't just pretend not to know anything to avoid getting involved in the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.78,0:04:25.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why did Andō-{\i1}san{\i0} kill Murobashi-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.45,0:04:30.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Weren't you two friends who escaped the fire together, five years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.45,0:04:31.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.45,0:04:34.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought so too, until two years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.87,0:04:40.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when I saw a painting at an auction that should've been lost in that fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.67,0:04:49.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I traced back the ownership of the painting, it eventually led back to Murobashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.18,0:04:50.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.85,0:04:53.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Murobashi-{\i1}san{\i0} stole the paintings from the mansion
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.60,0:04:57.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and set it on fire to hide the theft, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.10,0:04:59.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Causing a lot of victims in the process.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.94,0:05:00.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.82,0:05:10.87,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,If he, like the rest of us, boarded this train in memory of the magnate's family and the others who died in the blaze,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.87,0:05:13.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then I was planning to just force him to confess.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.29,0:05:23.67,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,But while we were waiting together as murderer and victim for the children playing the detectives in the fake mystery quiz,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.67,0:05:26.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he said this...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.93,0:05:29.26,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}These things are so exciting!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.26,0:05:32.06,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}They make you really feel alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.06,0:05:37.27,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Doesn't it remind you of that fire where we were trapped in the smoke and barely came out alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.81,0:05:45.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he said it so joyfully, his face flushed in excitement!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.87,0:05:55.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yukiko...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.24,0:05:50.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To think my wife suffocated in that fire in front of me...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.04,0:05:58.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You seem to want to cast a smokescreen over us,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.37,0:05:59.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but your chances of winning...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.96,0:06:01.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...are huge!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.04,0:06:04.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because Shin-{\i1}chan{\i0} got a hold of your weak point, Sharon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.84,0:06:09.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could that weak point be something about you being my friend, and therefore, untouchable?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.18,0:06:11.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your partners don't know, do they?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.51,0:06:16.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Shin-{\i1}chan{\i0} and that girl were de-aged by that drug.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.52,0:06:23.02,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,Despite the fact that if you narrow the search down to primary school age children, finding them would just be a matter of time...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.65,0:06:25.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin-{\i1}chan{\i0} told me...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.07,0:06:32.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...that there's probably a reason for you to hide that they became children again from the drug.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.83,0:06:35.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then there's...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.45,0:06:36.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suguru Itakura.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.37,0:06:40.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know him, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.46,0:06:47.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That CG creator who we actresses all knew from his work in movie special effects.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.51,0:06:53.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was shocked when Shin-{\i1}chan{\i0} told me that you'd ordered some kind of system from him. {deliberately using 'system' for sofuto since it's really a 'system-soft' aka operating system}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.22,0:06:59.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd heard from my actor friends that you clashed with him on some film set and had been at each others' throats since.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.19,0:07:05.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, you being you, you probably changed your voice when talking to him over the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.98,0:07:08.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that system you put so much effort into ordering...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.15,0:07:12.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does that have anything to do with why you're hiding their de-ageing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.03,0:07:15.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's enough, Yukiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.70,0:07:19.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.29,0:07:22.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've already seen through your ridiculous plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.71,0:07:24.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,P-Plan? What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.88,0:07:32.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When she learns that we're on board the train, there's only one thing she'll do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.72,0:07:36.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She'll take the antidote and go back to her normal body.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.14,0:07:43.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she was killed as a child and found on board,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.10,0:07:46.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,those children would cry and kick up a fuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.23,0:07:49.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if she went back to her normal form,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.69,0:07:52.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,even if they find her corpse,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.03,0:07:56.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then to the children, she'd just be a woman they once happened to meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.78,0:08:00.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They'd be more worried with finding their missing friend,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.95,0:08:04.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and would therefore be more likely to escape the Organisation's notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.37,0:08:09.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, your son and that Dr. Agasa will know otherwise,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.50,0:08:16.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but they'd never dare say that the corpse {\i1}was{\i0} their friend, as she looked before she became a little girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.93,0:08:21.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. You must've predicted that's how she'd react,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.81,0:08:24.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and you were going to take her in before she took the antidote.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.14,0:08:29.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you would've disguised as her and appeared to die in front of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.40,0:08:33.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,thus letting her escape the Organisation's eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.45,0:08:37.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the fact that she isn't in this room
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.16,0:08:41.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,means you haven't been able to take her in yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.04,0:08:43.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.21,0:08:47.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You looked into my suitcase before you threw it out, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.50,0:08:50.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you see any disguise kit in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.63,0:08:51.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.30,0:08:55.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I already got rid of it before I dealt with the suitcase.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.59,0:09:01.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The disguise kit you'd hidden in this washbasin,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.22,0:09:04.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,as well as the bulletproof jacket set up to release fake blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.89,0:09:09.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-But you haven't found her yet either, so you haven't won either...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.56,0:09:12.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No problem{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.86,0:09:17.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've already made preparations to smoke her out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.75,0:09:29.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Andō-{\i1}san{\i0}, let's leave the rest to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.67,0:09:32.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! What's all that smoke?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.38,0:09:35.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.38,0:09:37.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll check.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.18,0:09:41.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fire?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.30,0:09:42.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.81,0:09:45.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone, we have to evacuate to the front of the train!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.15,0:09:49.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wake up, Uncle!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.40,0:09:51.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You too, granny, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.19,0:09:54.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is an emergency announcement!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.48,0:09:57.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A fire has been reported in Carriage 8!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.49,0:10:00.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.20,0:10:01.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A fire?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.95,0:10:03.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\a6}For your safety, the passengers in Carriages 6 and 7 should evacuate to the carriages at the front of the train!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.24,0:10:05.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is Carriage 6, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.37,0:10:06.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.25,0:10:08.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then we better escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.08,0:10:12.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Calm down, everyone! Don't run, there's nothing to worry about!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.43,0:10:22.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as we thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.68,0:10:26.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All the passengers in Carriage 8 are pyrophobic.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.35,0:10:29.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They've stirred the place into quite a panic!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.39,0:10:30.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.85,0:10:32.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So here's the big question.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.77,0:10:35.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In this situation, where do you think {\i1}she{\i0}'ll go?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.90,0:10:38.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She'll run to the front carriages, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.11,0:10:42.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nope. Just the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.41,0:10:44.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What she'll do, is most likely...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.47,0:11:09.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You really are Hell Angel's daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.06,0:11:13.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You look just like her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.23,0:11:18.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A pleasure to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.03,0:11:25.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My codename is 'Bourbon'.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.53,0:11:37.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Mouri-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.82,0:11:40.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad! Where's Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0} and Sera-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.24,0:11:43.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The four-eyed brat was with me until just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.66,0:11:47.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I thought that tomboy went back to you some time ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.27,0:11:50.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,, She's not with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.17,0:11:52.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe she mistook which carriage she was in and got the wrong room...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.96,0:11:54.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.21,0:11:55.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's Ai-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.30,0:11:56.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She went that way, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.97,0:11:58.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't she with Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.89,0:12:01.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't she with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.26,0:12:04.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She went to the toilet and never came back!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.35,0:12:07.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then maybe she ran to a carriage further up?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.56,0:12:10.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what we thought, but we haven't been able to find her!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.40,0:12:14.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gah, brats are all the same...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.23,0:12:20.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. Knowing her, she'd go straight to Carriage 8, the source of the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.37,0:12:25.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She'll realise that the fire is a trap by us to draw her out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.08,0:12:31.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see! She thought you'd be waiting for her at the\N front of the train, so she went to the back instead!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.67,0:12:33.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't get it at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.67,0:12:38.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her friends will also be evacuating into the front carriages.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.26,0:12:41.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she, who's being targeted, goes there,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.51,0:12:43.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,they might end up getting involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.72,0:12:47.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why she'd decide to head into the fire instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.64,0:12:50.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if she knows we'll be waiting...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.31,0:12:55.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As she would prefer to die alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.61,0:13:01.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.28,0:13:06.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin-{\i1}chan{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.08,0:13:11.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, what's wrong, Shin-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.25,0:13:12.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mum! We're in trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.75,0:13:15.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't find Haibara anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.09,0:13:18.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is she with you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.76,0:13:21.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, she hasn't come to my room!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.30,0:13:23.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe she evacuated to the front of the train?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.64,0:13:27.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd be easier to hide herself in a crowd.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.22,0:13:29.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, I'll check the front.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.89,0:13:32.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mum, you stick to the plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.06,0:13:33.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.48,0:13:37.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With that, your son will also head to the front carriages.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.45,0:13:44.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And here's an e-mail from my partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.99,0:13:46.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm sorry,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.66,0:13:49.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but we seem to have found her in Carriage 8.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.46,0:13:54.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like we win.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.67,0:13:57.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,'Bourbon'.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.00,0:14:00.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you recall hearing this codename before?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.67,0:14:04.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've met your family before.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.05,0:14:06.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I've heard of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.85,0:14:12.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're a member of the Organisation, and the rival to my sister's boyfriend, Dai Moroboshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.52,0:14:16.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From what my sister told me, there was a lot of antipathy between you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.25,0:14:17.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.77,0:14:21.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as I suspected, he turned out to be an FBI dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.28,0:14:27.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't believe the reports that he'd been killed after betraying the Organisation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.45,0:14:33.62,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,So I disguised myself as him and wandered around people close to him, to watch their reactions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.25,0:14:39.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But all I could figure out from that is that he really {\i1}is{\i0} dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.17,0:14:46.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, my partner who helped me make that disguise is the one who's now disguising as him in my place.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.01,0:14:53.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fact that you've appeared before me shows how much she terrifies you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.40,0:15:00.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, would you put your hands up and slowly walk backwards?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.32,0:15:03.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll go to the luggage car behind Carriage 8.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.95,0:15:12.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One hour until the Bell Tree Express arrives!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.87,0:15:16.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Get ready, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.08,0:15:17.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a bunch of fools.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.75,0:15:24.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They have no idea that when the train arrives, they're gonna be blown to pieces by the bomb we've set on the platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.05,0:15:29.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of which, how are Vermouth and Bourbon gonna escape the train?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.72,0:15:32.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They know about the explosion, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.39,0:15:35.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows? Who cares?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.85,0:15:41.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Vermouth asked me if she could have some of the explosives, if there were any spare.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.15,0:15:42.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.44,0:15:47.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I asked her what she was going to do with them, but she completely evaded the question. {in before 'she went all 'secret makes woman woman' on me'}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.28,0:15:51.41,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That woman couldn't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.66,0:15:55.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, please open the door and head inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.50,0:16:00.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fear not.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.46,0:16:04.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I intend to take you back to the Organisation alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.17,0:16:09.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to destroy the link between these two carriages with an explosive, and break off the luggage car.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.72,0:16:14.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after it stops, my partners will come and collect you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.93,0:16:19.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until then, I'm afraid I'll have to knock you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.31,0:16:23.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.32,0:16:25.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll be sleeping at a safe distance from the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.99,0:16:28.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so you don't need to worry about getting caught in the explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.32,0:16:30.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apparently I {\i1}do{\i0} have to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.74,0:16:34.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This luggage car is full of explosives.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.66,0:16:39.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like there was a slip-up in your preparations.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.96,0:16:41.46,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.46,0:16:46.05,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Vermouth really {\i1}is{\i0} determined to kill her, no matter what...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.46,0:16:50.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Guess I have no choice. How about you come this way?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.13,0:16:52.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but I decline.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.01,0:16:56.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're as difficult as they said.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.47,0:16:58.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I might have to get a little rough with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.86,0:17:04.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Vermouth?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.36,0:17:06.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but she's coming with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.49,0:17:11.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A grenade?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.78,0:17:14.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who's there?! Who are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.33,0:17:21.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.89,0:17:36.01,Signs,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.10,0:17:37.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There. That's the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.77,0:17:40.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way! It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.02,0:17:41.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.23,0:17:46.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I waited for the sound of my partner destroying the link to the luggage car before I detonated the bomb,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.15,0:17:48.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so the train won't derail.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.98,0:17:50.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ai-{\i1}chan{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.86,0:17:56.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ai-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.25,0:18:03.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You killed Sherry?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.37,0:18:05.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure, Vermouth?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.88,0:18:10.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Bourbon watched her go up in smoke along with the luggage car.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.67,0:18:14.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because of that, though, the train was stopped at a nearby station.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.14,0:18:17.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We passengers are all going to be questioned by the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.14,0:18:21.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a shame I can't meet you at Nagoya, since you've been waiting so patiently.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.35,0:18:23.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's why you wanted the explosives.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.48,0:18:28.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If an explosion took place on board, they'd stop the train for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.90,0:18:29.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.40,0:18:33.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You {\i1}are{\i0} satisfied with just Sherry being blown to bits, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.61,0:18:36.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I was so surprised!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.57,0:18:39.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had no idea Haibara-{\i1}san{\i0} was in Carriage 7, Room B!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.83,0:18:43.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was free because it was the dead guy's room!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.62,0:18:47.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said she had to rest when coming back from the toilet because her cold was making her dizzy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.00,0:18:52.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Quiet. She's worn out, so she's getting some sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.01,0:18:53.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.55,0:18:55.59,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.59,0:18:58.51,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}They figured that if she'd run to a room, it'd be that one,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.51,0:19:00.64,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}so Yukiko was waiting for her there and hid her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.64,0:19:03.48,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So that kid's phone call back then...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.06,0:19:07.94,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It was an act trying to keep me stalled in Yukiko's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.44,0:19:11.44,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But wait — then who was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.44,0:19:14.57,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Who was the girl who blew up in front of Bourbon?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.03,0:19:18.28,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Don't tell me it was that special guest...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.37,0:20:47.79,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But wait — then who was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.79,0:20:50.87,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Who was the girl who blew up in front of Bourbon?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.37,0:20:54.75,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Don't tell me it was that 'special guest'...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.72,0:20:56.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This sucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.88,0:21:00.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now Kid-{\i1}sama{\i0} won't be able to come on board the train.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.05,0:21:03.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With all the crime scene investigations, they won't be able to use the train for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.64,0:21:04.80,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.80,0:21:07.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, sorry. Sounds like things heated up a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.77,0:21:11.94,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Don't tell me it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.86,0:21:17.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't sign up for this! What was with those dangerous guys?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.86,0:21:22.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I hadn't hidden my hang-glider in the luggage car just in case, I'd have been fried!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.61,0:21:25.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, since it's {\i1}you{\i0} we're talking about, I just figured you'd be prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.78,0:21:28.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, consider yourself out of my debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.58,0:21:30.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn right I am!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.12,0:21:34.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And remember to return that phone to the Detective Agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.79,0:21:37.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.88,0:21:40.30,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Damn brat...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.30,0:21:44.26,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You're really Kaitō Kid and his accomplice, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.26,0:21:46.76,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Is this a joke?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.76,0:21:50.22,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The maid, Sumitomo-{\i1}san{\i0}, is Kid,\N and the old lady is the accomplice.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.22,0:21:54.06,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}She doesn't seem to be able to mimic Komino-{\i1}san{\i0}'s voice, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.06,0:21:58.19,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Kid was using ventriloquism to make up for that, and she was lipsynching
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.19,0:22:02.07,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}while trying to mask it with the veil of her hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.07,0:22:06.45,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I see. That's why you made me run down the corridor.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.45,0:22:07.74,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.74,0:22:11.95,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I figured the old lady wouldn't be able to speak on her own.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.95,0:22:17.04,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And all the passengers rescued from that fire are pyrophobic,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.04,0:22:21.09,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}but the old lady happily lit up her pipe.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.09,0:22:23.55,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Anyway, be a little grateful.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.55,0:22:28.64,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I didn't press you guys when you were trying to avoid getting involved in the case by saying you didn't see anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.64,0:22:32.48,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Well? What sort of favour you trying to buy?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.48,0:22:37.77,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Disguise yourself as this woman, and\N shake off the bad guys going after her!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.65,0:22:44.24,Flashback,,10,10,0,,{\be10}Your conversation with them will be provided through an earphone, directly from her waiting in a separate room.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.24,0:22:46.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Out of {\i1}your{\i0} debt?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.99,0:22:50.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the one who's in {\i1}my{\i0} debt now, Detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.96,0:22:55.71,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.71,0:23:01.05,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That was indeed the ultimate cast, Yukiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.01,0:23:05.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sera-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.72,0:23:07.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm glad you're safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.13,0:23:09.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found this hat in the corridor.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.35,0:23:11.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's yours, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.14,0:23:13.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.93,0:23:17.14,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Why was it in the corridor?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.14,0:23:19.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone else is waiting, so let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.03,0:23:26.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The detailed files from the time of Akai's death...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.65,0:23:28.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can I see them one more time?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.61,0:23:29.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.74,0:23:35.29,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Looks like I'm going to have to restart investigating from square one.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.46,0:23:45.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't open the door!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.14,0:23:54.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So Mouri-{\i1}san{\i0} must be here too!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.47,0:23:59.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The corpse was blocking the door,  so how can this be a murder?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.73,0:24:02.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0} said, and he was inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.65,0:24:05.44,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And what's more, this is an impossible crime!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.94,0:24:08.45,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Another locked room murder?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.45,0:24:14.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the next Conan: 'Conan in a Locked Room'!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.54,0:24:19.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint: Special Coach!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.46,0:24:20.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\a6}Sonoko, why tennis training?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.50,0:24:22.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\a6}Gotta train myself in tennis and in love!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.38,0:24:24.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\a6}Wait... Love?
